`marshmallow-jsonapi` is great, but it appears to be missing support for the [document links object](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-links). I've hacked this into a schema with:

```python
class JiraSchema(Schema):
  def get_links(self, item):
    return {
      'self': api.url_for(Jira, jira_id=item['id'], _external=True),
    }

  def format_items(self, item, many):
    ret = super(JiraSchema, self).format_items(item, many)
    if many:
      for doc in ret:
        doc['links'] = self.get_links(doc)

    return ret

  def get_top_level_links(self, data, many):
    if many:
      self_link = api.url_for(Jiras, _external=True)
    else:
      self_link = api.url_for(Jira, jira_id=data['id'], _external=True)

    return { 'self': self_link }
```

But it'd be nice if there was formal support for it.

